main event: On September 15, 1966, observers in the California area reported seeing a bright round object flying low and visible for several seconds.
interesting points: The sighting involved multiple civilian observers,The object's movements included flying low and changing direction rapidly,One witness described the object as having a bright light and no color on the outside,The report indicated that the object was visible for only a few seconds,Detailed analysis suggested a possible meteor as an explanation.
witness description: Civilians from the area reported the sighting.
